# NativeWind Styles

Always use NativeWind `className` for styling React Native components. Avoid `StyleSheet.create` and inline `style` objects.

## Rules

- Use `className` with Tailwind utilities for layout, spacing, colors, typography, and borders
- Never reach for `StyleSheet.create` unless the style genuinely cannot be expressed in Tailwind (e.g. complex transforms, animated styles from Reanimated)
- Reanimated `Animated.View` / `Animated.Text` may use `style` for animated values — that is expected
- Dynamic dimension values that depend on runtime calculations (e.g. `Dimensions.get`) may use `style` — prefer `className` for everything else in the same element

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Good — NativeWind className
<View className="flex-row items-center gap-2 rounded-xl px-3 py-2 bg-accent">
  <Text className="text-sm font-bold text-on-accent">Hello</Text>
</View>

// ❌ Bad — manual StyleSheet
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: { flexDirection: 'row', alignItems: 'center', gap: 8 },
});
<View style={styles.container}>…</View>
```
